<item>
            <title>[GROOVY-9455] STC: no error for if (!(x instanceof T)) x.methodFromT()</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/GROOVY-9455</link>
                <project id="12318123" key="GROOVY">Groovy</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Variant of &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/GROOVY-6429&quot; title=&quot;flow typing detects unexpected error at if-else flow&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;GROOVY-6429&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;GROOVY-6429&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/GROOVY-8321&quot; title=&quot;!instanceof treated incorrectly in type checker&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;GROOVY-8321&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;GROOVY-8321&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/GROOVY-8412&quot; title=&quot;Support !instanceof flow typing for else case&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;GROOVY-8412&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;GROOVY-8412&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/GROOVY-8523&quot; title=&quot;Static type checking instanceof&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;GROOVY-8523&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;GROOVY-8523&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/GROOVY-8645&quot; title=&quot;ClassCastException after checking of instanceOf&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;GROOVY-8645&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;GROOVY-8645&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Consider the following:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-groovy&quot;&gt;
@groovy.transform.TypeChecked
void test(x) {
  &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; (!(x &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;instanceof&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;Number&lt;/span&gt;)) {
    x.byteValue() &lt;span class=&quot;code-comment&quot;&gt;// accidentally had &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;this&lt;/span&gt; and got no compiler error; STC has &lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;Number&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;for&lt;/span&gt; typeof(x)
&lt;/span&gt;  } &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;else&lt;/span&gt; {
    &lt;span class=&quot;code-comment&quot;&gt;// ...
&lt;/span&gt;  }
}
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Since the inferred type of &quot;x&quot; inside then block is Number, the IDE shows code assist for Number, which is misleading.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
